Response Text: HOT taxes will never be enough. There needs to be a significant effort put into increasing the HOT allotment (even a small percentage increase diverted from the Convention Center) and/or establishing other ways to fund arts & culture. Re-writing the grant guidelines every 2 years only causes more frustration, distrust and confusion around the process. It would be more beneficial to pay the local organizations, non-profits and individuals already doing the grassroots work instead of spending large amounts on larger institutions (The Long Center, Miles Partnership) who do not have a strong connection with the community and who are not held accountable. Capacity building and sustainability should always be at the forefront.

